snippet.textDisplay:
MacOS security hooplah Apple's claims:
"Check if only contains malware" - No, that would be a check against the app in their DB since it's the application hash, so if they detected malware and flagged it later they can argue this. 
"No user identifying information" - Based on the date, time, computer, ISP, city, state and application hash it should be quite possible to identify a unique user.
"Stepping up encryption" - There was no encryption at all, it's not stepping up, it's adding any.
"Will let users opt out in the future" - Why was this not instantly an option already? And these checks are done at boot,  this should be an opt-in feature with a message prompt to say you should opt in when you boot the machine for the first time.
No mention that this request doesn't actually go to Apple but rather Akamai (3rd party CDN)?

This should also have a lawsuit filed against them, it goes against the GDPR.
